### Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)

#### **Can a relationship survive if both partners have distinct trauma responses?**

Absolutely. In fact, many couples naturally match up in classic patterns, such as a "Fight" responder pairing with a "Freeze" or "Flight" responder. At **Riaz Counseling**, we teach you how to recognize each other's nervous system cues so you can help ground one another rather than escalating the trigger.

#### **How long does it take to see progress in healing trauma responses?**

Because trauma responses are deeply wired into the nervous system, sustainable recovery typically requires consistent commitment. Many clients at **Riaz Counseling** report experiencing a baseline reduction in relationship reactivity and an increase in emotional safety within $12\text{--}16$ weeks of structured, trauma-informed therapy.

#### **Does Riaz Counseling offer individual therapy for relationship issues?**

Yes. Sometimes the most effective way to heal a relationship is to do individual work first. By exploring your personal history, childhood attachment styles, and trauma triggers with a therapist at **Riaz Counseling**, you can fundamentally change how you show up for your partner.

